sub_title: Lecturer Marine Ecology @Wageningen University and Research
summary: People generally describe me as an enthusiastic, ambitious and motivated marine ecologist who commits herself to sustainable development. This is for instance shown by the fact that I was chief editor of a book on the role of biology in sustainable development (“Life Support”) during my biology bachelor. In this function I was responsible for the coordination of 18 co-authors, besides writing a chapter on sustainable food production. I also do not mind getting my hands dirty in muddy practical research projects. I for instance performed an individual research project on the production of extracellular polymeric substances by electrogenic bacteria in the seafloor for nine months, and I am currently working on the topic of natural mangrove regeneration. For this research project I will perform field experiments in Indonesia starting in August (2015).
